<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-75-0976 </DOCNO><TEXT>The formation of the angular distribution of amplified laser emissionin the case of nonaxial external signal injection into an unstable resonatorcontaining an active medium is investigated theoretically and experimentally.The possibility of the angular selection of the external signal is demonstrated.The analytical results obtained here agree with experimental data andmake it possible to estimate the role of frequency effects and determinethe requirements for maximizing emission selection. 12 references.</TEXT></DOC>